## IN PRACTICE Pragmatic and operational support Methodological resources and proven tools
combined with deep knowledge and understanding of the company for tailored support

### Contributing
to the alignment of the organization's and its actors' challenges Our approach is based on the co-definition and co-construction of a customised approach, adapted to the context, aimed at taking root in your organization's time and space

### Certified and experienced professional coaches
Professional coaches certified RNCP combining professional rigour and a variety of business experience Learn more and schedule coaching \* \* _

### Face to face and remote The feedback from the
months of confinement in 2020 showed that in most cases, individual executive coaching was done in a completely effective and calm way remotely. The fact that there is no commute time to manage and being in the space of your choice is particularly appreciated by many. Our programmes are therefore available both face to face and remotely. _ \* \*

## Benefits of coaching for companies A study by the
Deloitte firm in France showed that **94% of companies surveyed consider that coaching has a positive impact on their overall performance, particularly in terms of improving team performance and leadership development**. (Reference: "Coaching in business: State of the art and perspectives", Deloitte, 2018) According to a survey conducted by the International Coach Federation France (ICFF) among coaching professionals in France, **83% of respondents observed an improvement in the performance of individuals and teams following coaching support**. (Reference: "Coaching Barometer in France", International Coach Federation France, 2020) A study by the HEC Paris Executive Education firm showed that **companies that invest in coaching can achieve an average ROI of 300%, with performance gains observed in areas such as leadership, communication, stress management and time management**. (Reference: "Evaluation of individual coaching as part of leadership development: case study", HEC Paris Executive Education, 2014) A study by the Coaching Observatory in France revealed that **88% of the companies surveyed believe that coaching has a positive impact on their employees' performance, particularly in terms of skill development, motivation and job satisfaction.** (Reference: "Coaching Observatory in France - 2018 Edition", Coaching Observatory,

2018. According to research conducted by the Chamber of Mediation and Consulting (CSMC), French
companies that implemented coaching support observed **an improvement in internal communication in 73% of cases, as well as an improvement in individual and collective performance in 67% of cases**. (Reference: "Coaching, leverage for company development", Chamber of Mediation and Consulting, 2017)

